<br>
Most mobs usually considered in the same category or higher generally have a lot more hit points and usually less damage output. That means they're doable with less &quot;normal&quot; people than manaburn wizards. Vindi, Zlandicar, Klandicar, ST warders are on the next tier of hps. And all of those are doable with 18 people, which is less than the number of wizards you'd need. <br>
<br>
Sont was and is impressive (that is, if a dozen people clicking a button once can ever be considered impressive), but the paranoid people who are projecting that kill outwards to bigger and better kills haven't thought it through properly. IMO as soon as you need more wizards than a standard raid would require players, it's not a big deal anymore. If you can get 35-40 wizards together to kill some big mob, more power to you. I guarantee I'll have a much easier time getting my guild together to drop the same mob.<br>
<br>
*edit* King, queen, prince are single group killable. Who cares if it's 6 wizards, or a balanced group. <p><html>
